						               													<description>Mosquito Family is about assaulting unsuspecting people and pets with your mosquitoes to collect blood and increase popularity among mosquitoes.&amp;#10;But be careful, otherwise your mosquitoes will have to escape!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the game:&amp;#10;Have the most blood at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player Turn:&amp;#10;At each turn these steps must be performed:&amp;#10;1. Day or night&amp;#10;If you are the first to take a turn, in this round,  turn the Day/Night card over.&amp;#10;2. Assault a target&amp;#10;Choose an available Target card that has the  Blood face visible and draw Blood cards to assault a target. In case you draw a Look card, or you exceed tolerance limit of the target (based on the visible face of Day/Night card), stop immediately and the Angry face step begins. In the Angry face step, flip Event cards and try to run away!&amp;#10;3. Coming home&amp;#10;Place live Mosquito Tokens that have assaulted a target on the Player Card Blood Track, at the value equal to the amount of blood collected. You can place Mosquito Tokens over the others. Those Mosquito Tokens remain on the blood track until the final scoring.&amp;#10;4. Targets have recovered&amp;#10;If all the Targets Cards have the Angry face visible: turn them so that the Blood face is visible, keep the last 4 event cards and shuffle all the others face-down to form a new deck. In any case turn all Event Cards on the table face-down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;End of the game:&amp;#10;The game ends when all players have no Mosquito tokens to play.&amp;#10;The player with the largest amount of blood is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Single Player Mode and Cooperative Mode available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
